<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-29T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-29T20:00:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/311: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Marseille</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-29T20:00:00-05:00">March 29, 1937—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your 29th, arrest volunteers. Take up passports and request applicants
                            furnish names and addresses of persons who will supply funds for
                            maintenance and return United States. Cable result interview, including
                            French position in the matter.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>